            "problemDescription": "The progress bar is not functioning correctly. Identify and fix the bug in the code.",
            "language": "html",
            "buggyCode": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Progress Bar</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            font-family: sans-serif;\n            display: flex;\n            flex-direction: column;\n            align-items: center;\n            justify-content: center;\n            height: 100vh;\n            margin: 0;\n        }\n\n        .progress-container {\n            width: 300px;\n            height: 30px;\n            background: #eee;\n            border-radius: 15px;\n            overflow: hidden;\n            position: relative;\n        }\n\n        #progressFill {\n            width: 0%;\n            height: 100%;\n            background: #3498db;\n            transition: width 0.4s;\n        }\n\n        .controls {\n            margin-top: 20px;\n        }\n\n        button {\n            padding: 10px 20px;\n            cursor: pointer;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n\n<body>\n    <div class=\"progress-container\">\n        <div id=\"progressFill\"></div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"controls\">\n        <button id=\"prevBtn\">Back</button>\n        <button id=\"nextBtn\">Forward</button>\n    </div>\n\n    <script>\n        const fill = document.find('progressFill');\n        const next = document.getElementById('nextBtn');\n        const prev = document.getElementById('prevBtn');\n        let progress = 0;\n\n        next.addEventListener('click', () => {\n            progress = Math.min(progress + 25, 100);\n            fill.style.width = progress + '%';\n        });\n\n        prev.addEventListener('click', () => {\n            progress = Math.max(progress - 25, 0);\n            fill.style.width = progress + '%';\n        });\n    </script>\n</body>\n\n</html>",
            "solution": {
                "code": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Progress Bar</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            font-family: sans-serif;\n            display: flex;\n            flex-direction: column;\n            align-items: center;\n            justify-content: center;\n            height: 100vh;\n            margin: 0;\n        }\n\n        .progress-container {\n            width: 300px;\n            height: 30px;\n            background: #eee;\n            border-radius: 15px;\n            overflow: hidden;\n            position: relative;\n        }\n\n        #progressFill {\n            width: 0%;\n            height: 100%;\n            background: #3498db;\n            transition: width 0.4s;\n        }\n\n        .controls {\n            margin-top: 20px;\n        }\n\n        button {\n            padding: 10px 20px;\n            cursor: pointer;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n\n<body>\n    <div class=\"progress-container\">\n        <div id=\"progressFill\"></div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"controls\">\n        <button id=\"prevBtn\">Back</button>\n        <button id=\"nextBtn\">Forward</button>\n    </div>\n\n    <script>\n        const fill = document.getElementById('progressFill');\n        const next = document.getElementById('nextBtn');\n        const prev = document.getElementById('prevBtn');\n        let progress = 0;\n\n        next.addEventListener('click', () => {\n            progress = Math.min(progress + 25, 100);\n            fill.style.width = progress + '%';\n        });\n\n        prev.addEventListener('click', () => {\n            progress = Math.max(progress - 25, 0);\n            fill.style.width = progress + '%';\n        });\n    </script>\n</body>\n\n</html>",
                "explanation": "Fixed the incorrect method call or syntax error."
